SIMPLE: empress
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Empress
<hw>Em"press</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>empress</ets>, <ets>emperice</ets>, OF. <ets>empereis</ets>,
<ets>empereris</ets>, fr. L. <ets>imperatrix</ets>, fem. of
<ets>imperator</ets>. See <er>Emperor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
consort of an emperor.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A female sovereign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sovereign mistress.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Empress</xex> of my soul.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Empress cloth</b></col>, <cd>a cloth for ladies' dresses,
either wholly of wool, or with cotton warp and wool weft. It resembles
merino, but is not twilled.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Empressement</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
